leagues. Defiant Priests highlights a clerical culture that embraced violence to resolve disputes and seek revenge, to intimidate other men, and to maintain their status and authority in the community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aMarriagexReligious aspectsxCatholic ChurchxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aMarriagezSpainzCataloniaxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aMasculinityxReligious aspectsxCatholic ChurchxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aMasculinityzSpainzCataloniaxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 4aReligious Studies. 4aSpain.  aMasculinity, Medieval Iberia, Sexuality, Violence, Priests.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501707827?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501707827423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501707827/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles